annotation.TEXT: Yep, there are moving holes, and cutoff staircases, so I think raocow's name for this place is appropriate.
Looks like I'm piloting some sort of windy stony layer two-y vehicle here.
Alright, now as for where I'm heading next, 7-2 came in second in the voting, so let's check out this "Cold Bridge and Float Water"...
Yeah, I accidentally put "paczki" instead of "pączki" in the voting results last time. (Well, let's have those packages be filled with doughnuts!)
Fortunately, this wind isn't too strong for me to fight against, but I still should be mindful of it, obviously.

Yep, I'm back here, but remember those two brown blocks up near the ceiling in this room? Go to them and hit your P-switch. (Remember that this silver P-switch now acts like a blue one, which is what you'd normally have at this point.)

Ah, I'm falling for coins. But, since I have a cape, I can take it slowly, and have time to react to a ledge showing up and land on it.
That 1♥P would've been a little bit trickier to reach without a cape.

NOOO!!! That mushroom was way too fast for me, and I lost my flower...
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Now, which of these six levels will I be playing next?
Well, when you go this way, keep going to the left, past the P-switch door. (I wonder how long it would've taken me to find this if it wasn't for raocow's video...)
They're trying to shell me, man! Now, watch as I destroy their weaponry in a needlessly complicated way.
Really, man? That really happened?
Alright, that's enough of that. (I probably could've sped up a little of the footage here, but I didn't think of it beforehand. Oh, well. No big deal.)
Place your votes now, and... What the?!

I think this area is promoting stomping combos...

Now, this yellow pipe on the far right is where you're supposed to go.
Luckily, the reserve feather still worked after the fade out began!
Whoa, you kinda need a super koopa boost here.
Over to the right here is a star coin and a level-resetting door that I'm not going to enter.
Fart. Well, that was likely to happen with my impatience.
Whoa, don't slip up now!
I wonder if anyone can make some cool Touhou fanart in Mario Paint...
There's the last star coin. It would be easily reachable with the springboard, but I'm stubborn and want to use this block or a super koopa to reach it instead.
However, as you can see, there is also a stopping point in the middle of that path, and if you stand at that spot and press down...
Yep, there was a star coin up there.
BGM: New Super Mario Bros. (DS) - Castle Theme
Stomping a P-switch at the bottom of this room causes ? blocks to cover the spikes, but that's about it.
And, there we go! That was an interesting puzzle.

D'oh! And once again, a surprise mushroom has stolen a better reserve item from me.
Oh, man. It's a race situation. Me VS Eating Block! (So much more exciting than "You VS Boo"!)

This pipe is your target, and you want to carry a P-switch through it. Since I'm no longer double-grabbing, this silver P-switch will act like a blue one on the other side, which is what I'll need anyway.
And that block contains another cape, which is good because I suddenly need a replacement because I'm dumb.
Garf!

And this opens a path towards 4-B, and clears away the rock under 4-B's level dot.
Alright, I'm all caped up and ready to continue onwards.
Jittery camera movement FTW! Now let's go to the voting results and see what's what...
So, I guess whenever you see a ? block in this level, there will be a pop-up mushroom right below it.
And there's Bowser's Sky! So, where should I head next? 8-1?
Got it off screen. Alright, let's wrap this level up.

...Wheeee!!! You get to break the laws of SMW OW physics! Also, once you've done this once from the north, you can go through this mysterious hidden path by pressing up from 4-5, which will be a handy shortcut for me later! (You can do this even if you haven't revealed 4-5 from the south yet.)
Ha! That mushroom thought it could steal my flower, but I was too fast on the Select button for it!
Oh, this pipe is two-way. Interesting... Hey, this means I can block clone myself a silver P-switch!
There's another P-switch, and there's a star coin on the other side of the spikes over here.
Lalala♥ Time to blow up a castle!
If it wants me to "A", I'll "A"!
Oh, man. Did I just stick to the wall for a split-second there? That probably would've made it easy for me to wall jump if it weren't for the restrictive nature of my vehicle...
Oh, and these doors that you've seen along the way just reset the whole level if you enter them. I'll show off a couple right now, but I'll probably just ignore them later on.
Obviously, I want the star coins, but I'm pretty sure I can't waste too much time!

Oh, whoa! What is this? Wow, this is certainly interesting...
So, yeah. If I lost the race, the boss door would not have been enterable, and I wouldn't be able to finish the level. Alright, so let's battle Larry!

And that opens up 7-3, which is a red level. Now, I could've stopped the video here, but... 7-7 came in third in the voting, and I like the idea of playing another level before raocow gets to it! So, yes, I am taking on the seventh castle now!
Quick, gotta solve this simple puzzle!
To be continued...
